  'rx061':{ uses:'Treats major depression, obsessive-compulsive disorder (OCD), panic disorder, bulimia nervosa, and premenstrual dysphoric disorder (PMDD).', works:'SSRI antidepressant that increases the availability of serotonin in the brain by blocking its reabsorption.', side:'Insomnia, nausea, headache, diarrhea, sexual dysfunction, initial anxiety or agitation.', warn:'May increase suicidal thoughts in young people in early treatment — monitor closely. Do not take with MAO inhibitors. Takes 2-4 weeks to show full effect.' },
  'rx062':{ uses:'Prevents neural tube birth defects during pregnancy. Treats folic acid deficiency anemia.', works:'B vitamin essential for DNA synthesis, cell division, and healthy red blood cell production throughout the body.', side:'Very rare at this dose. May cause mild stomach upset.', warn:'Essential for women planning pregnancy — begin before conception. High doses can mask vitamin B12 deficiency.' },
